    {
      "id": "c86",
      "file": "c86.wav",
      "text": "Here is where I landed after the weekend. I found a much smaller model that is memory efficient, I got word bias working across every engine, and I wired the whole pipeline together so a dictation goes from speech, to the text stages, to an optional rewrite, and inserts atomically. It still takes a moment when there is a rewrite in the loop, but it is good enough that I have been using it every single day.",
      "source": "human",
      "tags": [
        "long",
        "proj"
      ],
      "condition": "noisy",
      "checks": {
